🌍 Language Detection with Python
This project demonstrates how to build a simple yet powerful language detection tool using the langdetect library in Python. With support for over 55 languages, the tool allows users to input any text and returns the detected language code.

🎯 Objective
To detect the language of a given text input using a pre-trained model from the langdetect library in Python.

⚙️ Technologies Used
Python
langdetect – Lightweight language detection library based on Google's language-detection algorithm
input() – For dynamic user interaction

🔌 Installation
pip install langdetect

🧪 How It Works
from langdetect import detect

text = input("Enter any text in any language: ")
print(detect(text))
Takes user input
Detects the language using detect(text)
Returns a 2-letter ISO 639-1 language code

Example: 'fr' for French, 'en' for English, 'es' for Spanish

📝 Example Output
Input:
Salut, je suis Anna Varma, j'espère que vous allez très bien.

Output:
fr

📌 Notes
langdetect can detect over 55 languages.
It may not be 100% accurate for short or ambiguous text.
For more consistent results, use longer and grammatically correct sentences.
